<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:pref="http://www.w3.org/2002/Math/preference" pref:renderer="mathplayer-dl"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><title>glXGetCurrentDrawable</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.69.1" /></head><body><div class="refentry" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="glXGetCurrentDrawable"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>glXGetCurrentDrawable — return the current drawable</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> GLXDrawable <b class="fsfunc">glXGetCurrentDrawable</b>(</code></p></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781958"></a><h2>DESCRIPTION</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glXGetCurrentDrawable</code> returns the current drawable,
            as specified by <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glXMakeCurrent</span></span>.
            If there is no current drawable,
            <code class="constant">None</code> is returned.
        </p><p>
            <code class="function">glXGetCurrentDrawable</code> returns client-side information.
            It does not make a round trip to the server.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4781862"></a><h2>SEE ALSO</h2><p>
